You are only updating forms. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the form property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating form in the description.

## form
All properties in the Description set are available for use with the form property.

Form types must be from the "form" controlled list.

### Resource type

Choose a value from the Library of Congress Resource Types Scheme (https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/resourceTypes.html):
- Artifact
- Audio
- Cartographic
- Collection
- Dataset
- Digital
- Manuscript
- Mixed material
- Moving image
- Multimedia
- Notated music
- Still image
- Tactile
- Text
- Unspecified

Every resource should have at least one type.

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "Text",
      "type": "resource type",
      "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/resourceTypes/txt",
      "source": {
        "value": "LC Resource Types Scheme"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### DataCite resourceTypeGeneral

Choose a value from the DataCite resource type list (https://datacite-metadata-schema.readthedocs.io/en/4.7/appendices/appendix-1/resourceTypeGeneral/).

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "JournalArticle",
      "type": "resource type",
      "source": {
        "value": "DataCite resource types"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### DDI General Data Format

Choose a value from the DDI Alliance Controlled Vocabulary for General Data Format (https://rdf-vocabulary.ddialliance.org/ddi-cv/GeneralDataFormat/2.0.3/GeneralDataFormat.html).

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "Numeric",
      "type": "resource type",
      "displayLabel": "Data resource type",
      "uri": "http://rdf-vocabulary.ddialliance.org/cv/GeneralDataFormat/2.0.3/8732239",
      "source": {
        "value": "DDI General Data Format"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Form

Form refers to the physical or material aspects of the original resource.

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "ink on paper",
      "type": "form"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "ambrotypes",
      "type": "form",
      "uri": "http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300127186",
      "source": {
        "code": "aat"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Genre

Genre refers to aspects of the content of the resource.

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "Oral history",
      "type": "genre"
    },
    {
      "value": "Documentary photographs",
      "type": "genre",
      "uri": "https://id.loc.gov/authorities/genreForms/gf2017027230",
      "source": {
        "code": "lcgft"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Extent

Extent refers to the size, dimensions, number, or duration of the resource.

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "33 pages",
      "type": "extent"
    },
    {
      "value": "12 cm x 15 cm",
      "type": "extent"
    }
  ]
}


### Internet media type

See the list of internet media types (https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml).

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "image/jpeg",
      "type": "media type",
      "source": {
        "value": "IANA media types"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Digital origin

See the list of MODS digital origin terms (https://www.loc.gov/standards/mods/userguide/physicaldescription.html#digitalorigin).

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "reformatted digital",
      "type": "digital origin",
      "source": {
        "value": "MODS digital origin terms"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Reformatting quality

See the list of MODS reformatting quality terms (https://www.loc.gov/standards/mods/userguide/physicaldescription.html#reformattingquality).

{
  "form": [
    {
      "value": "access",
      "type": "reformatting quality",
      "source": {
        "value": "MODS reformatting quality terms"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### Note

Additional information may be provided in a note, with an optional display label.

{
  "form": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "Reformatted in 2012.",
          "displayLabel": "Reformatting note"
        },
        {
          "value": "NTSC",
          "displayLabel": "Broadcast standard"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
